pageContext.claim: “When they sell a car into the United States, they pay 2.5% tax. When we sell a car into china, they don't want it. They have barriers. If they took it, it is a 25% tax. Think of it. Think of it. They have a tax that is 10 times higher. What they say is, we don't want your cars.”
pageContext.analysis: The tariff is 25 percent, but Trump is wrong to suggest no American cars are sold in China. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
